-> Static
    - In case of Humans, Population is something that will be same despite that human exist or not.
      For me it is 8 billion
      For you it is 8 billion

      soo this thing never depends on the object... hence it is Static

    - I want to explain the example in OOPs_Chapter_2.Human class
        * Try to understand this more carefully
        * Humans Object -> Population is static
        * In the constructor Human.population += 1 which means it is incremented by one everytime the constructor is called
        * You can access Human.population without any Object by default it will 0 since it is not long data type
        * Java runs line by line soo firstly it printed first "System.out.println(Human.population);" at that time population was zero because no object
        * Then we made "kush" and "rahul" object now it calls constructor and population was incremented twice and then we accessed it ofc it would *2*
        * Now it doesn't depend on Constructor but the Increment does... best example is the first print statement.. it did run and showed zero despite there is no object created yet.

    - Static methods are actually accessible without any object

    - Inside Static you cannot use anything that is non static.. why?
      Because Non Static is something belongs to particular class so without specifying you cannot access this method / variable but vice versa is possible.

    - Static in Static -> Allowed
      Static in NonStatic -> Allowed
      NonStatic in Static -> *NOT* Allowed
      NonStatic in Static -> Allowed

    - Cannot use this keyword inside keywords, because this belongs to class and static doesn't infact it doesn't use anything inside it that is non static

    - Outside class cannot be static because it is not dependent on any outside class

    - SingleTon class: Class that only has one instance / object.
        in order to make object we need constructor.. so if we somehow controlled the constructor then it will be only able to make one instance hence declare it as private


